    "@type": "MLModel",
    "name": "S-VAE",
    "description": "The Variational Auto-Encoder (VAE), while widely used, struggles to model data with a latent hyperspherical structure when using its default Gaussian distribution for prior and posterior distributions. To address this limitation, the text proposes an S-VAE (hyperspherical VAE) that uses a von Mises-Fisher (vMF) distribution instead, thereby creating a hyperspherical latent space. Experiments demonstrate that this S-VAE is better suited for capturing data with a hyperspherical latent structure and outperforms a normal N-VAE in low dimensions on other datasets.",
    "keywords": [
